Updates?

879
01:23:10,057 --> 01:23:12,479
No updates or announcements.

880
01:23:12,499 --> 01:23:23,467
You know, of course, Commissioner Kirsten is retiring after many, many years of valuable contributions and

881
01:23:26,622 --> 01:23:30,423
I don't know how to thank you enough for all that you've done.

882
01:23:30,443 --> 01:23:41,427
I know that my relationship with you is a lot newer than others, but I, you know, I've enjoyed my time with you.

883
01:23:41,447 --> 01:23:50,249
I do miss our chats, Commissioner Kirsten and I. There are some times we just catch up at, you know, as I'm schlepping home at seven, eight o'clock at night.

884
01:23:50,389 --> 01:23:53,770
And it's nice to get, it's really nice to get the other lens.

885
01:23:53,850 --> 01:23:54,751
And I definitely,

886
01:23:56,364 --> 01:23:57,705
I definitely value that.

887
01:23:57,825 --> 01:24:03,630
These are all things that are in the back of my mind as I do my work.

888
01:24:03,870 --> 01:24:06,412
So I thank you.

889
01:24:06,432 --> 01:24:07,773
Yes, I'll echo that, Marsha.

890
01:24:07,793 --> 01:24:09,615
I've enjoyed our conversations too.

891
01:24:10,235 --> 01:24:11,256
I hope they don't end.

892
01:24:11,396 --> 01:24:17,862
And actually, I wanted to thank you for your commitment to not only our commission, but I know you've had a

893
01:24:18,541 --> 01:24:22,044
long standing advocacy for the city of Medford.

894
01:24:22,104 --> 01:24:25,126
And I was with you before the city council.

895
01:24:25,207 --> 01:24:26,408
I know you've done that before.

896
01:24:26,528 --> 01:24:29,570
And I hope that you continue that work.

897
01:24:31,031 --> 01:24:31,412
Thank you.

898
01:24:31,472 --> 01:24:32,212
Thank you very much.

899
01:24:33,714 --> 01:24:41,480
I don't need to be saying, I want to say that I, I, this means a whole lot to me.

900
01:24:43,732 --> 01:24:49,236
because part of my life has been giving back to the community in different ways.

901
01:24:50,397 --> 01:24:58,162
And as I become older, I feel like I'm officially disabled now, for sure.

902
01:24:59,323 --> 01:25:07,348
And I want to say two things, that I welcome any of you to stay connected with me.

903
01:25:08,029 --> 01:25:11,671
As many of you as want, there's always Zoom in my heart.

904
01:25:13,351 --> 01:25:23,318
Second of all, if you want to have a social gathering on my patio and you promise to do it all on your own, there is a patio big enough for all of you.

905
01:25:24,379 --> 01:25:33,225
And it can be arranged as long as I'm physically able to, or mentally able, I guess.

906
01:25:33,786 --> 01:25:35,167
That's another disability.

907
01:25:37,769 --> 01:25:42,112
So I am grateful and I have enjoyed

908
01:25:43,136 --> 01:25:48,141
almost everything I do.

909
01:25:48,541 --> 01:25:51,664
And Tom, yes, he won't get rid of me.

910
01:25:54,446 --> 01:25:55,748
I hope not, Marsha.

911
01:25:55,828 --> 01:26:02,273
You know, I mean, I still think about that question, is being a senior a disability?

912
01:26:02,394 --> 01:26:04,836
You know, it's just... Now I have data.

913
01:26:05,596 --> 01:26:06,878
I have data from the CDC.

914
01:26:08,437 --> 01:26:11,278
48, 38% of seniors are disabled.

915
01:26:11,958 --> 01:26:13,878
So, yes.

916
01:26:16,239 --> 01:26:24,300
And just knowing, you know, you sharing just like some of what you've gone through in your life as you know.

917
01:26:25,401 --> 01:26:27,721
Marsha, you've shared your age before with us.

918
01:26:27,941 --> 01:26:31,822
Is it okay if I say your age or do you prefer I don't say?

919
01:26:31,982 --> 01:26:34,002
Marsha's 82 years old.

920
01:26:34,082 --> 01:26:34,223
Right.

921
01:26:37,065 --> 01:26:42,989
Marsha is two times, plus two decades, plus two of the ADA.

922
01:26:43,930 --> 01:26:53,477
And, you know, where we are now and what Marsha has, you know, seen and experienced as an elder amongst our mass.

923
01:26:54,489 --> 01:27:09,989
And where we could be in the future is, the knowledge is invaluable and I, you know, and you know like Marsha always pushes you know Marsha has always felt that the standards for the ADA are too low and Marsha is right.

924
01:27:10,558 --> 01:27:15,122
I mean, you basically just have to not be able to fold a piece of post-it.

925
01:27:15,882 --> 01:27:17,624
But we needed something, right?

926
01:27:17,824 --> 01:27:21,927
We needed something to create the threshold and we can launch from it.

927
01:27:22,808 --> 01:27:34,797
And now I am happy to see so many other areas of what I consider to be the authentic selves of people

928
01:27:35,267 --> 01:27:47,634
being taken into consideration as a disability and being respected, but in a manner that enables them to live lives with quality.

929
01:27:49,114 --> 01:27:53,337
And because I have people like Marsha in my corner, I don't stop just there.

930
01:27:53,357 --> 01:27:55,238
I'm like, oh, I can't rest.

931
01:27:55,538 --> 01:27:56,639
I gotta keep jogging.

932
01:27:56,699 --> 01:27:59,180
Marsha's chasing me, you know?

933
01:28:00,260 --> 01:28:02,021
And I appreciate that.

934
01:28:03,722 --> 01:28:04,703
I appreciate that.

935
01:28:05,051 --> 01:28:09,174
Well, I believe that you have to dream when you advocate.

936
01:28:09,815 --> 01:28:13,218
Think about Judy Neumann, Steve Grant.

937
01:28:13,838 --> 01:28:17,862
Something happens, it's never your dream.

938
01:28:19,403 --> 01:28:25,268
But if you don't dream and then do some part of it, then nothing happens.

939
01:28:30,553 --> 01:28:35,416
Thank you, Marsha, and we all hope to see you in October.

940
01:28:36,857 --> 01:28:46,223
I don't think I'll be able to be there because of my health issues from COVID, unless they magically go away.

941
01:28:46,804 --> 01:28:52,888
But I'll try to sit in in September in the meeting, and I'll try to keep my mouth shut.

942
01:29:00,218 --> 01:29:01,899
have any received the box.

943
01:29:02,479 --> 01:29:09,781
Yvette is going to work with me on photography and I hope something will come of it.

944
01:29:09,801 --> 01:29:11,842
There's no guarantee.

945
01:29:12,882 --> 01:29:16,944
And so she can be perfectly capable.

946
01:29:17,344 --> 01:29:17,924
Thank you.

